Heat the oil in a large pan over a medium heat. Fry the onion, garlic, ginger and chilli for 5 minutes until soft. Add the curry leaves and spices and cook for 2 minutes.Add the tomato pur√©e, chopped tomatoes, tamarind paste and prawns and just cover with water. Simmer for 10 minutes, until the prawns are pink and cooked through. Season with salt and pepper.Serve the curry in the hollowed out bread halves, garnished with the toasted coconut, fried curry leaves and herb cress.